Class EntityEventTree<E extends Event>

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.etree.EventTree<E>
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.etree.BranchingEventTree<E>
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.etree.EntityEventTree<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of event in this tree
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class EntityEventTree<E extends Event> extends BranchingEventTree<E>
A branching event tree whose expression is a fluent of type entity and will have several possible branches: one for each possible value the fluent could have, one where the fluent's value is unknown, and the irrelevant branch.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

      events - events whose preconditions are satisfied
      fluent - the fluent on whose value this tree will branch
      branches - maps each possible value of the fluent to a branch containing events whose preconditions require the fluent to have that value
      unknownBranch - events whose preconditions require the fluent to be unknown
      irrelevant - the branch of the tree containing events whose preconditions do not involve the fluent

  • Method Details

    • getBranch

      public EventTree<E> getBranch(Value value)
      Description copied from class: EventTree
      Event trees branch based on the value of their expression in some state. This method is used to get the branch of the tree for which the expression has the given value. When this method is called with null as its argument, it will return the irrelevant branch if one exists. If this tree has no branches for the given value, this method returns null.
      Specified by:
      getBranch in class BranchingEventTree<E extends Event>
      Parameters:
      value - the value of the tree's expression in some state
      Returns:
      the branch corresponding to the tree's expression have that value
